	The binding will expand anytime you type 'cc' even in other
words.  Use this replacement for /alias which allows args:

/def -i alias = \
    /if ( {#} < 2 ) \
        /quote -S /~listalias `/list -i alias_%{1-*}%; \
    /else \
        /let body=%-1%;\
;       The alias_* macro /shifts unless [alias=~"old"] at runtime.
        /def -i -ag -mglob -h"send {%1}*" alias_%1 = \
            /shift $$[alias !~ "old"]%%; \
	    /if ({*} =~ "") \
		%body%%;\
	    /else \
		%body %%*%;\
	    /endif%;\
    /endif


	Or you would be much better off just doing:
/def cc = cast cure critic %*
And typing /cc person to use it.

