You are confisuing regexps and globs.

Globs (the default), are similar to shell filename expansion:
?	match any one character
*	match 0 or more characters
[]	match one character from a given range
Globs are "anchored", that is, they must match the entire line.

Regexps:
.	match any one character
*	match the previous pattern 0 or more times
?	match the previous pattern 0 or 1 times
[]	match one character from a given range
()	for grouping, or %Pn grabbing
^	match beginning of line
$	match end of line
Regexps are not anchored; use '^' and '$' if you want to anchor them.


So what you want to do is this:

/def -mregexp -t'^You are zapped by (.*) and instantly drop it.$' getzap = \
    get %P1 

See: /help patterns

