I didn't like the answers you got. I'd prefer this:

/def -p1 -mregexp -t'You are zapped by.*( [^ ]+) and instantly drop 
it.' = get %P2 

This work this way: the pattern inside the paren will match any 
pattern consisting of a space followed anything except a space. 
Since I used a +, this "anything" must have at least one character, 
thus ensuring you'll get a word. Because the " and..." follows the 
paren, that word will be the word immediatly prior to " and...".

The .* right after "by" (there is really no space between by and the 
dot, that was not a typo) will handle the other words (if any).

