No, that will not solve that problem, because:

* means "zero or more of the character before this one"
               (Here, charatcer can also be a range, like [A-z])

+ means "one of more of the character before this one"
               (same...)

This gives that you should use [A-z]+ to catch a name, if you use
a * instead of +, the trigger will also match "looks at you" (that is,
a line without a name first), and will send "look at" back to the MUD,
which is bound to confuse the MUD.

No matter which one you use, though, you will still end up with
"The red devil looks at you", making the client send "look at The red devil".
If your MUD can't handle that, then you need some additional technics to
avoid sending more then one word. See earlier postings in this list (very
recently, this was discussed) for more details.

