You can write your own macros.  /set quiet=off so you don't conflict
with the builtin stuff.

/def -Ttiny.moo -F -hCONNECT quiet_hook_moo = \
    /def -w -Fp11 -n20 -mglob -ag -t"*" quiet_gag_${world_name}%; \
    /def -w -Fp10 -msimple -t"*** Connected ***" quiet_end1_${world_name} = \
        /purge quiet_*_${world_name}
    /def -w -Fp10 -t"### end of messages ###" quiet_end2_${world_name} = \
        /purge quiet_*_${world_name}

On worlds defined with "/addworld -Ttiny.moo", this will gag 20 lines
or until "*** Connected ***" or "### end of messages ###", whichever
comes first.

