Defining a macro named "test" is a very bad idea, since it overrides
the builtin command.  In this example, your /test calls /test, so it
will recurse infinitely (or until %max_recur is reached).  (You can
always call the builtin with the /@name syntax even if there is a macro
with the same name, but it's still always a bad idea to redefine
"test").  Since you didn't mention this problem, and the problems you
described would not happen with this macro (even if you renamed it), I
must assume you didn't actually try the macro exactly as listed above,
and so there must be other differences which affect the behavior you
saw.  If you want debugging help, you must list EXACTLY what you tried.

