Hi,

> I type LLL, and it will: look east %; look west %; look sout %; look north

Two possibilities:
* define a macro called LLL:
  /def LLL = look east %; look west %; look sout %; look north
  You start it by typing "/LLL". That's the vesion with least overhead.
* /load alias.tf and define an alias called LLL:
  /alias LLL look east %; look west %; look sout %; look north
  You start it by typing "LLL". It created a send hook, which is a 
  trigger that checks everything sent to the mud and acts if the text 
  sent matches the alias name, which means some overhead. On the other 
  hand it's easier not to type the slash and I never reallized any slow 
  down from my aliases (not too many though).

I hope this helps,

