I would do it like this:

/def leader = \
   /def -mregexp -t'^%1 attacks (.*)\$' t_autoattack = kill %%{P1}

If you start grouping, you type "/leader <leader>" telling tinyfugue whom
to assist. This macro then defines a trigger triggering on the (complete)
line "<leader> attacks <the mob>" and sending "kill <the mob>" to your
MU*.

