Well, there's two ways that come to mind to get around this. One only works
 in THIS situation, and I tend to use it.

@@ is a null command on most TinyMushes, but not on a lot of other servers.
  Anywhere it ISN'T, I just define (or ask for it to be defined) as such.

On MUCK's, I @link an @action to the NULL.MUF command that's a library 
 function, or ask a friendly wiz to add it to the global defnition of the
 command.

On Mushes and Mushes where it's not defined as such, I define a $@@: attribute
 somewhere.

On MOOs...well, I don't go on MOOs. :) But I'm sure it can be done. :)

On anywhere else? See as per MOOs. :)



The second idea, though, comes to mind at the end of 'help hooks' (as only 
 hooks and triggers do anything with WORLD type, according to /addworld).

It gives an example of:

	/def -t'tiny.mush' -hSEND mush_escape = /send - ${/escape \%[ \%*)

That's designed to escape all occurances of \ [ and % on any line going to
 a 'tiny.mush' world, and then send the escaped line instead, to avoid 
 parser problems (in certain circumstances, like pages and says when you don't
 WANT them to be evaluated).

Well, then, this same sort of thing should be able to work for this problem.

It should be possible to use the SEND hook, to parse out, say @@ from all
 tiny.muck worlds, and send nothing....or send something equivalent if it can
 be found...

Of course, this is just the opposite of what is being looked for...my idea 
 is exclusive, not inclusive, and requires lots of /hooks if you have lots
 of world-types...but, it seems like it should work.

That is, if one of you more erudite types could like, code it up. :) I lost
 track of tf's macro language about version 2. :)

