The correct way to echo with attributes/colors is with /echo -a, like this:
"/echo -aCyellow -aCbgred TEST".  See /help echo, attributes, color.

"/set emulation=raw" will allow codes to pass through to the screen
uninterpreted by tf, which would (probably) produce the desired effects
from your original command, but also has many undesirable effects on
word wrapping, triggers, etc.  I recommend keeping the default value of
emulation=ansi_attr.

BTW, the next version will most likely have a way to change echo attributes
at any point in the line.  A command like
