If all you want to do is send a command to every connected world, you can
just use /send. Here's a command I use to quit from all worlds normally
without them thinking I went linkdead.

/def q=/send -W QUIT%; /quit

And for anyone that wants to do something similar, I set this as my
adisconnect, so whenever I don't quit with QUIT, it gives the message.

@adisconnect me=@swi %0={netdeath},{:has gone linkdead.}

As for sending to all worlds of a certain _type_, maybe that's something
that can be added to tinyfugue for /send.

Here's one possible solution... although sloppy, is workable. I got tired
of typing WHO in all caps for TinyTIM, so i made an alias for that world
so i only need lower case who now. You could make an alias for each world
to catch a command sent by yourself, such as who, and then in each alias
expand it to it's proper needed command (WHO, @who, or what have you) and
send it.

/def -ag -wTim -h"SEND {who}*" alias_who=/send -wTim WHO %-1


