certain type. the main problems in accomplishing this are:

1) /send doesn't have a -T option and
2) You can't get world type or other info from any world except the current
one. (unless you want to parse /listworlds, but that gets ugly)

On most server types, sending OUTPUTPREFIX by itself shouldn't do anything
harmful. and is silent, So see if this will work:

/def -T'tiny.mush' -h'send OUTPUTPREFIX' sendwho = who%; /send -W
OUTPUTPREFIX%; /undef sendwho

you could also add another /def to send @who or whatever else.
I tried it with just /send -W by itself and hooking send {}, but that just
doesn't want to work. Ah well.


