I didn't quite follow the discussion completely lately.
But I recall reading about somebody wanting to send a text
to all lp-worlds.

There is a (not so hard) way to do this:

/require grep.tf

/def selectname = /echo %{L3}
/def listlp = /quote -S /selectname `/grep lp /listsockets
/def sendlp = /quote -S /send -w`"/listlp" %{*}

The first macro will select the name field (third-last) from /listsockets.
The second macro will list all worlds of 'lp'-type.
And the last macro will send a text to all worlds listed with /listlp.

So now you can send a text to all lpworlds with just:
/sendlp <the text to send>

Note: it assumes that "lp" will only appear in the type field of
/listsockets.
If you use hostnames or worlds like "help", the above may not work.
In this case, replace the grep in the second macro by something more
intelligent; e.g. /egrep [^a-z]lp /listsockets


