Always name your triggers.  That said, tf doesn't directly match pairs
of lines.  Make a second trigger to match after you've seen the first.

/def -p1 -F -mregexp -t'ugga buggaa bogga\'$' bogga =\
    /def -p101 -F -mregexp -t'^You feel an aura' bogga_aura =\
	say Aura Up!%;\
    /def -p100 -1 -F -t'*' bogga_miss =\
	/undef bogga_aura


This version will make a trigger, and if you don't see the aura line
kill that second trigger.  You may need to adjust priorities to your
personal trigger environment.


