There is a way to solve the multiple line trigs problem. If I find 
some time later today, I may write the lib version of the solution.

The idea is using states, the same way many regexp pattern matching 
programs, such as lex, mailagent and, I think, awk do. This could 
probably be added to TF source code without much trouble, but I don't 
think, nor do I expect, to see this feature added before 3.5 release.

The syntax would be something like:

/def -t'first line' name = /state 2
/def -t'second line' -s 2 name2 = /state 3
/def -t'third line' -s 3 name3 = etc...

Obviously, you should use different states for every multiple line 
pattern. 

