When you want to in/exclude a litteral ']', you must put it in as
the first character. Any '\' will be seen as a litteral '\' character
(it has no special meaning at this place).

So the second line should read:

/test regmatch("\[([^]]+)\]", "[foo]") & echo(P1)

If you want to exclude any more characters, put them _after_
the '^]'.

