This is because of a tf workaround for a limitation of LP mud prompts
(see "/help prompts" for details).  If you don't explicitly define a
world as LP, tf will try to automatically detect them and /set lp=on,
but will not turn it off when you leave that world.  The best solution
is to use the -T'lp' option of addworld (see "/help /addworld") to
explicitly define your world types; then tf will turn /set lp=off when
you're on non-lp-prompt worlds.

