> It doesn't seem to want to accept the %L8 anymore. So my question is, how
> can I reference a variable name within a function, and eval, and
> operation, or whatever where the name consists partially of another
> variable?

The $[] is expanded because it's in the macro body; the outer %{} is expanded
becuase it's in $[]; but the inner %{} is not expanded because it's inside
%{}, which does not do expansion.  To force extra expansion, use /eval
and the right number of escapes (eg, extra %'s):

  /eval /echo $$[%%{hp_%{L8}}]

See the /help topics: evaluation, substitution, /eval

