You didn't say what you're trying to do, and I don't feel like taking
the time to carefully analyze your (overly) complicated code, but I
think your problem is a basic misunderstanding of how TF interacts with
a mud.  TF's code runs synchronously within itself (except for /quote
and /repeat); but not with the mud.  TF itself has no way of knowing
what (if any) results a mud will generate when you send it a command.
To TF, mud input and output are two unrelated streams of text.  If you
want to get the results of a mud command, you need to set up triggers to
deal with all possible mud outputs, before sending the command.

BTW, here's one bad practice I noticed:
>     /if /test $[regmatch(str_search,area_name)] =~ "1"%; /then

* Use =1, not =~"1", to test an integer result.
* regmatch() returns a 1 or 0, which is conceptutally "true" or "false";
  comparison is unnecessary.
* There's no need to nest $[] inside /test.
* "/if /test ... /then" can be simplified to "/if (...)".
Thus:
      /if (regmatch(str_search,area_name))

