This query about purging backspam reminds me of a
question/request/whatever I had in mind. I do/did admin on several MU*s,
many of which had a Substantial Collection of channels. One of the
features in TF that made my life easy was the hilighting of channels: I
could 'color-code' my channels and simplify the task of pulling pertinent
information from a screenload of text.

Well, as long as I've only got one world going, this is okay. But when I
bring up world 2, the first sign of activity will be an '% Activity in'
message, followed by a stream of spam telling me about '% Trigger in'. Now
I know I can disable this by turning off background processing, which is
really a rather nice way to handle things...but if I do, I get no activity
warnings.

Similarly, if I don't turn off background processing, my hilighting
triggers will apparently 'overlap' and all colored text will emerge with
the color of the most recent trigger on it, not the color which it should
have. This also happens when I've got '/more' running.

For example:

/hilite Creation*
/hilite GAME:*=/set hiliteattr=Cred
Creation pages: hi                  # this line shows in boldface
---- World tir ----
% Activity in world bal
% Trigger in world bal
---- World bal ----
Creation pages: test                # now it's in red
GAME: Destruction has connected     # as is this

Make sense?

Anyway, the question is simply: is there a way to turn off that goofy '%
Trigger' spam without turning off the '% Activity' notice? If not, could
we add one?

Secondly, is there a way to make the stuff in backscroll spam color
properly?

