Prompts are assumed to fit on one physical line.  If you try to make a
prompt wider than the screen, only the last physical line of it will be
displayed (that is, the last (length mod wrapsize) characters).  This
may be considered a bug, but multi-line prompts are not particularly
useful or common, so I intentionally did not bother to support them.
You're trying to use it for something it wasn't intended for anyway.

> 	My second problem is that the /prompt line (2nd from bottom) doesn't 
> seem to be working anyway. I can't even get it to pass pure text. What am 
> I do wrong here?

If the length of your /prompt argument is an integer multiple of %wrapsize,
you won't see anything, for the reasons given above.  For lengths less than
%wrapsize, /prompt works as advertised.

