a bunch of variables and initializes them to 0. Then, it sets up a bunch
of triggers to set the variables to 1 if I'm affected by a spell, and
then it casts the missing spells, at last it unsets the vars, undefs the
triggers. You could use a similar thingie. Because tf has no way of
knowing it should wait with casting the spells until the 'affect' list
is completed, you should tell yourself something after the affect and
trigger on that message. Of course, this script does not solve your
problem right away, but it's a start you can work with.




