Okay, here is something that i would find really useful for TF:

How often did you fall off a cliff, b/c you hadn't noticed your fly ran
out? How often have you been wondering if your paladin had his ability
to lay hands restored? It's so easy to miss a crucial message even if
it's hilited, so I thought it would be helpful to display flags as part
of the status line.

Example:

/def -ag -t'You rise up off the ground.'     xfly = /xset 0 F 
/def -ag -t'You sink gently to the ground.' rxfly = /xset 0 _

The first line would display an F at position 0 in the status line,
whereas the second would reset it to _ again, so one could see at one
glance whether the character is flying or not.

I have implemented it in a quick & dirty way *) into my TF and it works
great. It is so much easier to keep track of my magical protections etc.

Well, maybe if others like that idea too, we can convince Ken to
officially implement it. ;-)

