"Edward A.I. Copland" <set452@Winnie.freenet.mb.ca> writes:

> 	How would I get a /repeat to go to all the worlds I'm currently 
> on?

If you are just wanting to send some text to all the worlds, you can use 
/send -W in your /repeat.

Otherwise, let's say you want to emulate:

/repeat -W -TIME COUNT COMMAND

You can use:

/def command_in_all =\
    /let body=%{*}%;\
    /command_in_all_ $(/listsockets -s)

/def command_in_all_ =\
    /while ({#}) \
	/repeat -S -w%{1} 1 %{body}%;\
	/shift%;\
    /done

And then: /repeat -TIME COUNT /command_in_all COMMAND

So `/command_in_all /echo ${world_name}' lists the worlds you are on.
And `/command_in_all /echo -w ${world_name}' echoes each world name to
that particular world.  (Be sure to backslach special forms when needed.)

