It's a feature.  The More counter resets only for /dokey newline (i.e.,
you hit Return or Enter).  This is usually what is wanted; you probably
wouldn't want it to reset while you're in the middle of typing a line,
(including line editing keybindings) because your attention is on the
input window/line, and you may not have seen output that appeared while
you were typing.  TF doesn't try to decide when you want to reset and
when you don't; it only resets on newline.

If you want to reset the More counter at other times, you can
do it yourself with this /reset_more macro:

  /def reset_more = \
      /if (more & !moresize()) /set more=0%; /set more=1%; /endif

and use it like:

  /bind ^W = /reset_more%; /fg ->

