> would look like:
> 
>   <current world>______________B:____C:____M:____F:________(Log) etc...
> 
> And if there were any unred lines in the worlds corresponding to the 
> B,C,M, or F... it would look like:
> 
>   <current world>______________B: 1__C:23__M: 4__F:________(Log) etc...
> 
> While I can get the first version up and running, I can't seem to get the 
> variables to update properly...

To cause an update, you must change the value of the monitored variable.
But in this case, there's an extra twist:  if you simply have a '*' trigger
that changes the variable with nactive(), the nactive() will still return
the old value.  This is because triggers run _before_ the line is printed
or counted by nactive() (it has to be that way, so the triggers can apply
their hilites and gags).  So, you need to delay for an instant (e.g., with
/repeat -0 1) until the line makes it to the output queue.

First, stick "act_NAME:6" fields into status_fields, one for each world you
want to monitor.

Then define this:

  /def -Fp2147483647 -mglob -t'*' -hWORLD -q update_activity = \
      /repeat -w -0 1 
          /set act_$${world_name}=$$[strcat(substr($${world_name},0,1), ":", 
          nactive($${world_name}))]

A trigger on every line updates the field for the world.  A WORLD hook also
causes an update, so bringing a world into the foreground sets the field back
to 0.

> Oh, and I was wondering how to redefine the 'time' format at the end of 
> the status bar too.

Change %status_int_clock.

