writing two triggers that match the same part, but only highlight
different areas of it, like this:

/def -p100 -T"tiny.mush" -F -P1Cblue -t'(\().* looked at you.*\)$' TINY.MUSHlook
/def -p100 -T"tiny.mush" -F -P1Cblue -t'\(.* (looked at you.*\))$' TINY.MUSHlook2

It's something that I personally hate.  I'd MUCH rather have the
last colour be the one that was used.  Or even the first colour,
as long as it's defined I can juggle priorities to change the order
so I get the colours I want.


