When the mud sends an untermined prompt quickly followed by a line of text,
there is absolutely no way to separate the two.  This is a design flaw in 
mud prompts.  You may be able to reduce this by lowering prompt_usec, but
you can never get rid of it completely as long as lp=on.

The only complete solution is to convince the mud admin to add the GOAHEAD
or EOR prompt terminators as described in tf's "/help prompt protocol".
Then, you can run tf with lp=off.

