If you do a 'echo $MAIL' on the command line of your unix shell, you'll
get something like '/var/spool/mail/jblosser'
The command /sys executes all the following on the shell. So you can
type on TF command line:
  /sys egrep "^From |^Subject" $MAIL

and will get (for example):

!From blah@fasel.org Mon Dec  8 11 11:58:04 97
!Subject: Re: your spam from fasel.org
  
To cause that line only to print the last received mail, you can improve
the trigger:

   /sys egrep "^From |^Subject" $MAIL | tail -2



